title.narrative: Maximizing Impact for key populations affected by HIV

description.narrative: Lao (Peoples Democratic Republic) - HIV - Ministry of Health of the Lao People's Democratic Republic - MOH. This program has the following goals: To end the transmission of HIV and alleviate the impact of AIDS in LaoPDR. The objectives of this program are: To prevent and reduce the further transmission of HIV infection particularly among women sex workers and men who have sex with men, in priority provinces. To increase coverage and improve quality of treatment, care and support services for people living with HIV
